cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.FL

The paper deals with proof theory and decision procedures for grammar logics, which are a type of modal logic. This makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep inference, which is a technique commonly used in automated reasoning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses context-free grammars and regular languages, which are topics in programming languages and formal languages, respectively, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with structural rules and cut-elimination, which are topics in proof theory and logic, making cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category as well.
